{
  "text": "Rat hippocampal neurons used for electrophysiological and mRNA targeting experiments were cultured 8-9 days after plating, as described previously [CITATION_1] . RNAi pool specific for exon 6 was generated from the transcript of BDNF by PCR amplification of a 210-nt-long segment (167 nt + the T7-RNA polymerase sequence at the 5 0 end) with low levels of homology to other genes and high scores as targets for silencing as evaluated with the software 'siRNA Target finder' (Ambion). Primer sequences targeting BDNF rat exon 6 (GenBank: EF125680.1) are as follows: exon 6-T7 forward, 5 0 -GCGTAATACGACTCACTATAGGGC GGCTTGGAGAAGGAAAC-3 0 ; and exon 6-T7 reverse, 5 0 -GC GTAATACGACTCACTATAGGGGAGTCACATTGTTGTCA CGC-3 0 (Proligo). To obtain synthetic siRNA pool, doublestranded RNA was synthesized using T7-RNA polymerase with the corresponding mixture kit (Ambion) and digested with RNaseIII (Ambion), which generates oligonucleotides of 12-15 base pairs in length, which have been shown to be just effective as the longer Dicer 22-mer products. Detailed description of primers and analysis of siRNA efficiency was reported previously [CITATION_2] . We used the scramble siRNA duplex (Ambion), which has no effect on neuronal morphology and survival, as a control. Primary hippocampal neurons were transfected with the siRNA pool for exon 6 BDNF or scramble siRNA at 6 days in vitro using Lipofectamine 2000 (Invitrogen) following the manufacturer's recommendations and treated with drugs 3 days later.",
